        <div class="body">
            <p>Actually, this should not be honored.</p>

<p>If the user wants to use lowercase attributes, then simply make sure the keys are appropriately cast before you use the helper. However, there are some situations where case <em>does</em> matter. Some JS toolkits differentiate based on case, and will not function correctly if cast to all lowercase. Regardless, <em>no</em> browser today will balk at mixedCase attributes.</p>

